Sello Theletsane & ANA JOHANNESBURG- The Port Elizabeth High Court dismissed Athol Trollip’s urgent application to overturn his exit as the mayor of Nelson Mandela Bay on Thursday morning. The dismissal of Trollip’s application means that the United Democratic Movement’s (UDM) Mongameli Bobani in charge of the Nelson Mandela Bay municipality as the mayor. A motion of no confidence was tabled against Athol Trollip last month and passed by the NMB Council. DA councillor Mbulelo Manyati’s membership was discontinued after he decided to abstain his vote during the motion, this resulted in Trollip and the DA taking the matter to court.